Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.38,0:00:06.69,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Travel across the oceans of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.71,0:00:09.07,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellow a battle cry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.09,0:00:17.09,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Once your heart feels refreshed,\Nlet the signal to set sail ring out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.89,0:00:26.53,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We've left the established course
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.55,0:00:29.96,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, we're rowing straight toward
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:35.50,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,The borderline between the sky and the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.52,0:00:41.77,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,In the dark depths of the ocean,\Nadventure holds its breath
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.79,0:00:48.73,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have a good time just imagining it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.75,0:00:53.06,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Travel across the oceans of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.08,0:00:55.39,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellow a battle cry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.41,0:01:03.41,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Once your heart feels refreshed,\Nlet the signal to set sail ring out
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.44,0:01:12.62,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,"That feeling" I get when embarking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.64,0:01:16.21,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something I hope to remember always
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.23,0:01:21.76,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can, I won't be afraid of anything
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.78,0:01:27.97,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,With our pulses racing, \Nlet's go on a trip now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.99,0:01:35.02,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Shy hearts engrave the rhythm of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.04,0:01:39.15,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Snatch up the treasure here and there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.17,0:01:41.61,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,While laughing out loud
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.63,0:01:45.99,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,As we dash by like a noisy party
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.01,0:01:48.95,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Make some waves...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.97,0:01:50.74,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Life is "Adventurous"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:52.21,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Be aware it's "Dangerous"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.23,0:01:53.87,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's gonna be "One of us"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.89,0:01:55.50,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,And a trip goes on because
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.52,0:01:57.25,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We da pirate of the "Mass"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.27,0:01:58.96,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,To the West, To the East
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.98,0:02:00.46,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta find my way, Sail away
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.48,0:02:01.63,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,All the way to "One piece"!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.65,0:02:05.76,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Stuff a dream into your empty chest
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.78,0:02:08.18,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,And spread your wings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.20,0:02:12.47,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,If the wind blowing through\Nthem dyes your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.49,0:02:14.98,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's press forward
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:18.91,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Snatch up the treasure here and there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.93,0:02:21.27,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,While laughing out loud
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.29,0:02:25.49,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,As we dash by like a noisy party
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.51,0:02:33.51,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Make some waves...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.88,0:02:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time is the Great Pirate Era.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.99,0:02:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Countless pirates fight \Ndesperately for the One Piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.13,0:02:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the great treasure left behind by \NGold Roger, King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.80,0:02:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monkey D. Luffy, a boy \Nwhose body turned to rubber
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.74,0:02:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after he ate the Gum-Gum Fruit,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.68,0:02:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,also takes to the sea to become \Nthe next King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.49,0:02:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As Luffy and his friends \Novercome numerous adventures,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.49,0:03:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the World Government is less and \Nless able to ignore their existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.47,0:03:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.87,0:03:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of adventure \Nis waiting for us next?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.14,0:03:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The crew, on its way to the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.29,0:03:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will speed along the Grand Line again today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.74,0:03:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After landing on the Sabaody Archipelago,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.86,0:03:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Straw Hat crew succeeded in \Nrescuing the kidnapped Camie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.06,0:03:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, a battle began \Nwith marines lying in wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.49,0:03:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all set to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.00,0:03:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The group then attempted to break \Nthrough the navy's siege and escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.53,0:03:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Roger and Rayleigh\N-- The King of the Pirates and His Right Hand Man"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.30,0:03:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alive, Peterman-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.72,0:03:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare they do this to our boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.99,0:03:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.31,0:03:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn them!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.96,0:03:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.69,0:04:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected Duval to have such \Na handsome face under that mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.34,0:04:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see ya! Feel free \Nto call us again anytime!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.46,0:04:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be at your beck and call until you \Ncan safely set sail for Fish-Man Island!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.78,0:04:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Thanks, you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.70,0:04:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.50,0:04:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just quit winking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.82,0:04:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and one other thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.83,0:04:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget this, Miss Mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.27,0:04:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! My backpack!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.03,0:04:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That idiot Peterman had it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.26,0:04:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.90,0:04:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's go, Life is Rosy Riders!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Hand-Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.43,0:04:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their shouts sure change a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.38,0:04:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably trying \Nto find one that clicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.03,0:04:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then. Let us hurry inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.81,0:04:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get Hachi into a bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.66,0:04:57.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shakky's Rip-Off Bar"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.12,0:05:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shakky! I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.07,0:05:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, welcome back, Ray-san. That \Nwas sooner than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.16,0:05:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed you guys managed to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.17,0:05:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ol' Hachi's been seriously hurt. \NWe need to get him into a bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.36,0:05:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.78,0:05:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad! I'll get a bed ready right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.55,0:05:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you said you had something \Nto tell me afterward, old guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.36,0:05:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.65,0:05:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the Pirate King's ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.39,0:05:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm Silvers Rayleigh, \Nthe ship's vice-captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.28,0:05:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.37,0:05:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vice-captain?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't tell them, Hatchan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.32,0:05:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only needed his help \Nwith the coating, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.29,0:05:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You didn't realize it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.96,0:05:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know his name so well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.17,0:05:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's in so many books!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.51,0:06:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely a name everyone \Nhears at least once...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.43,0:06:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold Roger...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.07,0:06:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to vaguely recall a rookie named \Nthat long ago, but I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.27,0:06:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do such a big-shot and \Nan octopus know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.58,0:06:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi rescued me over 20 years ago, \Nwhen I was stranded in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.90,0:06:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He saved his life. He was still \Na child at the time, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.70,0:06:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi and I remained close after that, \Nuntil he joined the Sun Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.85,0:06:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Arlong, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.96,0:06:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.47,0:06:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though Gold Roger was \Nexecuted 22 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.87,0:06:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you didn't get your head chopped \Noff for being vice-captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.01,0:06:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The navy caught the entire crew, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.32,0:07:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We weren't caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.42,0:07:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger turned himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.20,0:07:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The government might've made it \Nsound like they had caught him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.03,0:07:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a way to show its power, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.63,0:07:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The King of the Pirates \Nturned himself in?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.38,0:07:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because we saw an end to our journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About four years before the \Nday of his public execution,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger caught a fatal illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.12,0:07:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even Roger could avoid the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.84,0:07:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that this terminal, \Nincurable disease brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.42,0:08:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, there was one man with the \Nskill to ease his suffering:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.44,0:08:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a man at the Twin Capes named Crocus,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.72,0:08:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who was the most respected lighthouse \Nkeeper and doctor in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.15,0:08:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We asked for his help and brought him \Non as ship doctor for our final voyage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.40,0:08:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, three years later, \Nwhile managing to escape death,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.15,0:08:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger achieved what was \Nsaid to be impossible:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.53,0:08:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he conquered the Grand Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.75,0:08:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-C-Crocus-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.86,0:08:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the Twin Capes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.82,0:08:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that brings back memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.76,0:08:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! That old guy wasn't \Nthere for 50 years straight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a member of the Pirate King's crew?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.78,0:08:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, he did mention \Nbeing a ship's doctor for a few years!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.02,0:08:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was a pirate for \Nthose three years, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:09:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that you've met him \Nmust mean he's still doing well!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crocus agreed to come aboard
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.08,0:09:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because there was a certain group \Nof pirates he wanted to look for.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.54,0:09:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brook! It was you guys he set \Nout to find, no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.16,0:09:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crocus-san...! You even \Nwent to such lengths...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.67,0:09:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was only a crewmember for three years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.08,0:09:21.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he was unquestionably one of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.25,0:09:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this age now, it'd be \Ngreat to see him again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.75,0:09:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what happened after he conquered the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.89,0:09:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when it all began.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.98,0:09:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world started calling \NRoger "King of the Pirates."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.37,0:09:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He hadn't been King of the Pirates \Nthe entire time before or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.49,0:09:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Titles hold no meaning \Nfor a man about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:10:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Roger was overjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.17,0:10:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He loved doing everything in a flashy way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.15,0:10:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether it was celebrating or fighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.68,0:10:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He even seemed to enjoy thinking \Nout a plan for the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.79,0:10:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even though he wouldn't be a part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.13,0:10:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, as per captain's orders, the \NRoger Pirates were secretly disbanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.43,0:10:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One by one, everyone discretely left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.21,0:10:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As comrades, we all risked \Nour lives together,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.85,0:10:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I know almost nothing about where \Nthey are or what they're doing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.10,0:10:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, about a year after we disbanded,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.29,0:10:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger turned himself in and was arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.81,0:10:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was then announced that \Nhe would be publicly executed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.64,0:10:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in Loguetown, the East \NBlue town he was born in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.19,0:11:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that many of the young \Nfaces in the town square that day
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.82,0:11:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,went on to make names for themselves \Non the high seas today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.86,0:11:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world focused its attention \Non the Pirate King's execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.29,0:11:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't attend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The final words he said went like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.39,0:12:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to die, partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.31,0:12:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The World Government and the \Nnavy must've been shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.04,0:12:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With only one last remark from Roger,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the public execution meant to serve \Nas an example to other pirates
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.35,0:12:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,instead became the opening \Nceremony of the Great Pirate Age!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.44,0:12:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.18,0:12:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want it, you can have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.42,0:12:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.43,0:12:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I left everything this \Nworld has to offer there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.30,0:12:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In his last few seconds, he \Nchanged the dim flame of his life
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.23,0:13:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,into a hellfire that spread across the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.99,0:13:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never laughed as much \Nas I did on that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.45,0:13:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor have I ever cried as much...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.23,0:13:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...or drank as much as I did on that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.61,0:13:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our captain lived one hell of a life!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.99,0:13:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like we just heard something incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.21,0:13:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost like a different story, \Nhearing it from someone who was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.89,0:14:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's almost as if Roger created \Nthis Great Pirate Era on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.71,0:14:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That... we still can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.31,0:14:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.85,0:14:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the people living \Nnow can create this era.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.79,0:14:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain there are people who \Ninherited something from Roger
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.19,0:14:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on that day in the town square.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.53,0:14:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your good friend, Shanks, \Nis probably one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.20,0:14:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? You know Shanks, old guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.67,0:14:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you also heard of the East \NBlue pirate known as Buggy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Buggy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.96,0:14:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two of them were apprentices on our ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.12,0:14:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Shanks was on the Pirate King's ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? He didn't tell you about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.64,0:14:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran into him again on these \Nislands about 10 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.72,0:14:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he'd lost his trademark straw \Nhat, along with his left arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked what had happened, \Nhe cheerfully spoke about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.42,0:15:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a real shock, Rayleigh-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.52,0:15:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a kid in East Blue who said \Nthe same thing Captain Roger did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.81,0:15:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those same words of our captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.38,0:15:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I've wanted to meet you-- \NMonkey D. Luffy-- ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.75,0:15:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.46,0:15:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid I can't, in good mind, babble \Non about things Shanks hasn't told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.05,0:15:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you've done \Nwell to come this far!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.27,0:15:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he's eagerly waiting \Nfor you in the New World.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.26,0:15:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! Do you think so?! I \Ncan't wait to see him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.53,0:15:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then. Let's get down to business.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.07,0:15:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted your ship coated, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:15:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should get back to my real work, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.06,0:16:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, coating \Ncosts a lot of money...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.65,0:16:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's all right, Hachi. I can't \Ntake money from friends of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.58,0:16:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a relief. Thank you, Rayleigh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.39,0:16:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno why, but he's doing it for free!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.01,0:16:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate it! You're one generous guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.27,0:16:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like we just saved a ton of money!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.18,0:16:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rayleigh-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.15,0:16:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a question!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.43,0:16:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly is the "Will of D"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.69,0:16:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger's name was engraved in ancient writing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.32,0:16:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on Poneglyph I saw on a sky island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.72,0:16:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How was he able to use that writing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.16,0:16:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I made it here. I will guide this \Ntext to the ends of the earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.72,0:16:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Pirate Gol D. Roger"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.83,0:16:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you people know what happened to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.58,0:17:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,during the Blank Century \Nthat began 900 years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.14,0:17:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.82,0:17:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We learned the entirety of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.87,0:17:31.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Miss. You mustn't be hasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.21,0:17:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continue to move forward one \Nstep at a time on your own ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.77,0:17:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We-- and Ohara-- might have \Nhurried a bit too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.82,0:17:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I told you everything \Nabout history right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.62,0:17:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you still wouldn't be able to \Ndo anything as you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.67,0:17:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you've taken the time to see the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.98,0:17:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's possible you'll be led to \Na different answer than we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.78,0:17:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if you still insist on hearing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.75,0:18:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell you everything \Nabout this world right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.27,0:18:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'll pass. I'll continue my journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.52,0:18:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will all come into sight someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.60,0:18:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for what happened \Nto your homeland of Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.37,0:18:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Roger didn't decipher that writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.03,0:18:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.90,0:18:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't possibly match \Nthe intellect of geniuses
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.03,0:18:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like Clover and the scholars of Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.98,0:18:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He heard the voice of the \Nuniverse, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.79,0:18:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, are you sure, Robin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.66,0:18:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you didn't just \Npass up an incredible chance?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.64,0:18:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, old guy! There's one \Nmore thing I wanna ask!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.58,0:18:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The legendary great treasure, the One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.00,0:18:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.87,0:19:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.89,0:19:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna know where the treasure is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.83,0:19:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna know if the \Ntreasure exists or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.43,0:19:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've put all our lives on \Nthe line and set out to sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.14,0:19:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even though we don't know anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.44,0:19:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather give up being a pirate than \Nhave the old guy tell us stuff now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.44,0:19:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't go on a boring adventure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.79,0:19:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-S-Sorry! I knew that, but it \Njust slipped out of my mouth...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.28,0:19:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't wanna know, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.26,0:19:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I forgot! I have the "I'll Die If \NI Learn About the One Piece" disease!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.69,0:19:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, old guy! Don't say anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.11,0:19:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you can do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.31,0:19:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Grand Line still far surpasses \Nanything you can imagine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.07,0:19:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your foes will be powerful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.01,0:20:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you rule this mighty sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.62,0:20:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna rule anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.00,0:20:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the freest person in this sea \Nwho's the King of the Pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.48,0:20:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.30,0:20:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really am a fan of yours, Monkey-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.66,0:20:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your ship is in Grove #41, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.81,0:20:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll head over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.48,0:20:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.80,0:20:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There could be an admiral on \Nthese islands as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.59,0:20:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll only be a nuisance if we stay here,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.30,0:20:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so maybe we should go shopping somewhere?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.62,0:20:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this, "Laid-Back Life"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.32,0:20:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're being chased! We gotta hide, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.75,0:20:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The people chasing us might \Nshow up if we all stay together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.36,0:20:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll help him finish the work more \Nsmoothly if we lay low in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.51,0:20:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's just split up and then \Nmeet back there when he's all done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.57,0:21:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who're you to talk strategically about \Nmeeting up and stuff like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.99,0:21:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shakky. Do we have any?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.05,0:21:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there's one left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.25,0:21:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a Vivre Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.42,0:21:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, if you know what it is, \Nthat simplifies things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.19,0:21:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I happen to be a bit notorious myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.61,0:21:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll move it from Grove #41 to \Nsomewhere else before I start on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.44,0:21:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll need three days to complete the coating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.40,0:21:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It takes three whole days?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.96,0:21:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your life depends on this work. \NIt's the fastest I can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.41,0:21:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's three days of \Nwilderness survival then!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.35,0:21:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How frightening!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.31,0:21:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sundown in three days, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.09,0:21:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what grove I'll be on then, \Nso wherever the Vivre Cards lead you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.53,0:21:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be there finishing the \Ncoating and waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.38,0:21:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should probably also \Nbuy whatever you'll need
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.00,0:21:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for your underwater voyage \Nto Fish-Man Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.76,0:21:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy-chin! Everyone! Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.75,0:21:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Thanks so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.20,0:21:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I caused you so much trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.65,0:22:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't thank you guys enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.64,0:22:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll show you the way to Fish-Man \NIsland, so don't worry about a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.94,0:22:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out for the navy \Nfor the next three days!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.43,0:22:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi! Get plenty of bed rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.81,0:22:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet again in three \Ndays. We'll see you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.62,0:22:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later, lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.10,0:22:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're up against an admiral! We gotta \Nmake sure none of us gets killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.62,0:22:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say unlucky things like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.14,0:22:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three days, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.63,0:22:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.92,0:22:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the amusement park!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.03,0:22:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.34,0:22:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A navy warship's been \Nspotted from the harbor!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.48,0:22:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The admiral's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.20,0:22:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Kizaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.08,0:22:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.11,0:23:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.35,0:23:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the admiral really coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.38,0:23:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to meet him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.76,0:23:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one we met before, Aokiji, was crazy \Nstrong with that freezing Devil Fruit power!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.37,0:23:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear! I bet the other \Nadmirals have powers, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.51,0:23:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.47,0:23:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.96,0:23:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"No Escape!? Admiral Kizaru's \NLight Speed Kick!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.57,0:23:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
